[H-1]  `_wire_section` injected but never called — streaming silently broken
Files: backend/check_runner.py
       backend/check/cvim_checks.py
       backend/check/ocp_checks.py
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Problem:
  CheckRunner._run_checker() does:
      checker._wire_section = self._wire
      return await checker.run()
  The intent is that run() calls self._wire_section(sec) on each SectionResult
  to attach the asyncio.Queue before the check function executes, enabling
  real-time per-item streaming to the browser.

  But neither CVIMHealthChecker.run() nor OCPHealthChecker.run() ever calls
  self._wire_section(). Sections are created and handed to check functions
  without the queue ever being attached. Every sec.pass_()/fail_()/warn_()
  call inside every check runs _push() on a None queue, silently dropping
  all events. Real-time streaming never works.

Broken code (in CVIMHealthChecker.run() and OCPHealthChecker.run()):
  sec = Section(name, cat, start_time=datetime.now())
  # _wire_section is never called here
  try:
      await fn(sec)

Fix:
  sec = SectionResult(name, cat, start_time=datetime.now())
  if hasattr(self, '_wire_section'):
      sec = self._wire_section(sec)
  try:
      await fn(sec)


