[H-6]  `_check_certs` runs up to 160 sequential SSH commands — extreme latency
File:  backend/check/ocp_checks.py → _check_certs()
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Problem:
  The certificate check iterates over up to 80 TLS secrets and fires
  2 sequential await ssh.run() calls per secret (one to fetch the cert,
  one to calculate days remaining). With a 15s and 10s timeout respectively,
  this single check could take up to 80 × 25s = 2000 seconds (~33 minutes)
  in the worst case. It blocks all subsequent checks in the section list.

Broken code:
  for line in lines[:80]:
      r2 = await self.ssh.run(..., timeout=15)
      r3 = await self.ssh.run(..., timeout=10)
      # up to 160 sequential awaits, no concurrency

Fix:
  Use asyncio.gather() with a Semaphore to parallelise:
      sem = asyncio.Semaphore(10)
      tasks = [check_one_cert(ns, name, sem) for ns, name in secrets[:40]]
      await asyncio.gather(*tasks)
  Or reduce the scope to lines[:20] with a 5s per-command timeout.


