[M-5]  `_check_vms` pass/warn/fail branches can contradict each other
File:  backend/check/cvim_checks.py → _check_vms()
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Problem:
  The check contains:
      (sec.pass_(f"All {active} active VMs running")
       if active == total - shutoff - error
       else sec.warn(f"{total-active} VM(s) not ACTIVE", ...))
      if error > 0:
          sec.fail(f"{error} VM(s) in ERROR state")

  When active=5, shutoff=3, error=2, total=10:
  - active == total - shutoff - error → 5 == 10-3-2 → 5 == 5 → True → sec.pass_()
  - then: error > 0 → sec.fail()
  Result: both PASS and FAIL items appear in the same section, which is
  confusing and likely not the intended behaviour.

Fix:
  Separate the three concerns explicitly:
      if error > 0:
          sec.fail(f"{error} VM(s) in ERROR state")
      if shutoff > 0:
          sec.warn(f"{shutoff} VM(s) SHUTOFF")
      if active == total - shutoff - error:
          sec.pass_(f"{active} active VM(s), {shutoff} shutoff, {error} error")
      else:
          sec.warn(f"Unexpected VM state counts: active={active}, ...")


